Sentencas: The three-phase boundaries (TPBs) in the electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) have different activity because of the distributed nature of the electrochemical reactions.
Titulo: Electrochemically Active Thickness of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Electrodes: Effectiveness Model Prediction

Sentencas: The electrochemically active thickness ( EAT) is a good measure to evaluate the extension of the active reaction zone into the electrode and the effective utilization of TPBs.
Titulo: Electrochemically Active Thickness of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Electrodes: Effectiveness Model Prediction

Sentencas: In this study, an electrochemical reaction/charge conduction problem is formulated based on the Butler-Volmer reaction kinetics and then numerically solved to determine the EATs for the active electrode layers of SOFCs with various microstructural, dimensional, and property parameters.
Titulo: Electrochemically Active Thickness of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Electrodes: Effectiveness Model Prediction

Sentencas: Thus, the EAT data and correlations presented in this study are expected to provide useful information for designing efficient electrodes of SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrochemically Active Thickness of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Electrodes: Effectiveness Model Prediction
